  "concept": "vuejs/core#9285: `class and style merging` conflict with vue.template.compilerOptions.whitespace preserve",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:35.494906+00:00",
  "text": "`class and style merging` conflict with vue.template.compilerOptions.whitespace preserve\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.4\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/github-gjgfy8\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nVite 4.4.9\r\nset option compilerOptions.whitespace = \"preserve\"\n\n### What is expected?\n\noption compilerOptions.whitespace and style and merging work correctly\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nif we leave a comment before the first element in the template\r\nstyle and class merging do not work\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
